<apex:page showHeader="false" standardStylesheets="true" tabStyle="Process__c">
    
    <style>
        body {background: url('{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, "/inPageClouds.png")}') top left no-repeat;}
        a {text-decoration:none;}
    </style>
    
    <apex:pageBlock mode="maindetail" title="Introducing Processes">
        <apex:pageBlockSection columns="2" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p>
                    A Process is a single, logical program with inputs and outputs in the form of Messages.
                    Logic that splits data, combines data or alters data should be encapsulated in distinct processes.
                    When a process receives and acts on a message, it may output multiple new messages that go to subsequent processes.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Processes are implemented as Apex classes.
                    The Enterprise Service Bus framework ("ESB") contains by default a number of ready-made processes, including:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Schedule</li>
                    <li>Publish and Subscribe</li>
                    <li>Branch and Jump</li>
                    <li>Subsequence</li>
                    <li>Audit and Wiretap</li>
                    <li>Mark and Gate</li>
                </ul>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <apex:image value="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Process/processArtifacts.png')}" />
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p>See the tutorial: <a href="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/ProcessDiscoveryTutorial.html')}"  style="color: #00f;">How to discover EDA Processes</a>.</p>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="List View Buttons" columns="1" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Process/discoverProcesses.png')}" /> can be used to find new Processes. Click this button after authoring or installing Processes to make them available.</p>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="Detail Page Buttons" columns="1" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Process/viewApexClass.png')}" /> will show you the Apex Class that contains the underlying logic for any given Process.</p>
                <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Process/viewSettings.png')}" /> takes you to the available Settings for a Process. (<b>Note:</b> Not all process have Settings)</p>
                <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/Process/viewDocumentation.png')}" /> shows the supporting documentation provided by the author of a given Process.</p>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>  
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection title="Click [Continue] to proceed." columns="1" collapsible="false" />
    </apex:pageBlock>
    
    <apex:pageBlock mode="maindetail" title="Discovering Processes (continued below)">
        <apex:pageBlockSection columns="2" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p>Before a process written in Apex can be referenced as a step in a sequence, 
                    it must first be discovered and registered in the Enterprise Service Bus framework.
                </p>
                <p>This discovery job will be launched automatically when installing the package or trying to build a Sequence for the first time.</p>
                <p>There is also a mechanism for discovering processes manually and is initiated by clicking the [Discover] button from the Processes list view.</p>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
        <apex:pageBlockSection columns="1" collapsible="false">
            <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                <p>Learn more about <a style="color:#00F;" href="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/ProcessDiscoveryTutorial.html')}">Process Discovery</a> within the ESB framework.</p>
            </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
        </apex:pageBlockSection>
        
    </apex:pageBlock>
    
</apex:page>